==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amaryllis
<hw>Am`a*ryl"lis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Amaryllis</ets>, Gr. <?/, <?/, the name of a country girl in
Theocritus and Virgil.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A pastoral
sweetheart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To sport with <qex>Amaryllis</qex> in the shade.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A family of plants
much esteemed for their beauty, including the narcissus, jonquil,
daffodil, agave, and others.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A genus of the same
family, including the Belladonna lily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amass</ent>⟦br⟧
